<item>
            <title>[SPR-11929] JMX Bean to allow monitoring Spring Websocket</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-11929</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There needs to be some JMX bean to allow applications to monitor the state of Websocket connections.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is already implemented mostly in the samples:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/rstoyanchev/spring-websocket-portfolio/blob/master/src/main/java/org/springframework/samples/portfolio/config/JmxConfig.java&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/rstoyanchev/spring-websocket-portfolio/blob/master/src/main/java/org/springframework/samples/portfolio/config/JmxConfig.java&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It should be factored out and exposed as an MBean by Spring so applications can use it without needing to know the internals of Websockets implementation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
